parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Liner Delamination and Rusting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delamination and rusting of the fuel tank liner can cause the fuel tank to fail, leading to stalling, loss of power, and potentially leaving the driver stranded, which can lead to accidents or safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
fuel filters become clogged with debris
rust particles are found in the fuel system
and the fuel tank liner detaches from the inner structure of the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Excessive Heat Generation in Front Passenger Compartment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive heat generation in the front passenger compartment can cause discomfort and potentially lead to burns or injuries, especially during prolonged driving periods.
symptoms: The front passenger compartment floorboard heats up to extreme temperatures (160+ degrees)
making it unbearable for the passenger to keep their feet on the floorboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving at an undetermined speed
requiring the driver to take the vehicle to a mechanic for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power windows can cause inconvenience and discomfort for the driver and passengers, and in some cases, may obstruct the driver's view, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The power windows fail to go up and down
the power windows make an abnormal clicking noise
the power windows are stuck in an open or closed position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the dome lighting can reduce visibility inside the vehicle, making it difficult for the driver and passengers to see, especially at night or in low-light conditions, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The dome lighting fails to turn on
the dome lighting is dim or flickering.
